{
  "rewrites": [{ "source": "/(.*)", "destination": "/index.html" }]
}
```

This is a static site so Vercel handles it automatically, but this file makes routing explicit.

---

## Step 5: Share It

Once your repo is live, people can find and use it via:
- The **Deploy to Vercel** button in your README
- Directly downloading the ZIP from GitHub (`Code → Download ZIP`)
- Forking the repo and editing it themselves

---

## Summary Flow for Someone Using Your Template
```
Click "Deploy with Vercel" button
        ↓
Vercel forks your repo to their GitHub
        ↓
They edit index.html with their own info
        ↓
Push → Vercel auto-redeploys
        ↓
Live portfolio at their-name.vercel.app
